serves 6 — good for easter / mother's day

- 2-2.5kg lamb shoulder (bone-in or rolled)
- 5 large potatoes, peeled & mandoline-sliced
- 1 large onion, mandoline-sliced
- 500ml lamb or chicken stock

[ glaze 1 ]
- 1 tsp dijon
- 4 tbsp evoo
- sea salt
- rosemary & thyme leaves
- 2 crushed garlic cloves
- juice of 1 lemon

[ glaze 2 ]
- 1 tsp honey
- 1 tsp miso
- 1 tsp dried oregano
- 4 tbsp boiling water

- oven to 160°C
- layer potatoes & onion in a tray, lamb on top
- score the meat 1cm deep
- rub glaze 1 over the lamb, pour stock around it
- cover with foil, bake 4-5 hours until tender
- up to 180°C, brush on glaze 2, baste potatoes with pan juices
- uncovered 20-30 mins until golden
